The Edo State Government has announced the commencement of the revalidation exercise for pensioners in the 18 Local Governments Areas (LGAs) of the state. A statement by Permanent Secretary/Chairman, Pensions Bureau, Mr. Saylor Juwobor said the ‘AM-ALIVE Revalidation Exercise’, will hold from Wednesday 18th to Friday 20th December, 2019 at 9:00 am daily. All affected pensioners were further directed to be physically present with the following documents: Biometric slip, Bank Verification Number (BVN), Pension Identity Card, and Pension Authority. The Statement reads, “This is to inform the general public that the Edo State Pensions Bureau in conjunction with the Information Communication Technology Agency (ICTA) will be conducting AM-ALIVE Revalidation Exercise for all Edo State Pensioners in the 18 Local Governments Area of the State from Wednesday 18 to Friday 20 December, 2019 at 9.00 am daily”. It added, “The venue for the screening of Pensioners resident outside Benin City will be at the Local Government Council’s secretariat nearest to them while pensioners in Benin City are to be at Urhokpota Hall, Oba Ovoramwen square, Benin City.” Vanguard News Nigeria Some pensioners in Edo State have saluted Governor Godwin Obaseki's courageous move to clear all the pension arrears he inherited. October 14, 2018 In "News" In continuation of the payment of pension arrears to Edo State Government retirees as agreed with pensioners in the state, the Edo State Government is set to pay the arrears of nearly 200 pensioners after the Wednesday December 20 and Thursday, 21, physical and documentary verification for batch 39 of pensioners at the… December 17, 2017 In "News" The Edo State Government has invited pensioners in batches 43 and 44 for physical and documentary verification in order to process payment of their pension arrears. May 19, 2018 In "Business"